Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{600%g} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Pick the @rosemary{1%unit} leaves and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Pop the potatoes onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Toss with half the rosemary, @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{}.

Spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn the tray halfway through.

Finely chop the @hazelnuts{10%g}.

Surround the @Irish chicken breast{320%g} with #cling film{} or #baking paper{}.

Bash with the bottom of a #pot{} until it's 1-2cm thick. Season with salt and pepper.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Beat the @egg{1%unit} in a #bowl{}.

Mix @breadcrumbs{1%pack}, hazelnuts, remaining rosemary and @salt{½%tsp} in another bowl.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? This is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Dip the chicken into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

Place a large pan over high heat with enough @oil{} to coat the bottom.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden-brown, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly—heat for 2-3 mins before adding the chicken.

Transfer the chicken to a lined baking tray.

Bake on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Discard the excess oil from the pan and give it a quick wipe (you'll be using it again).

== Creamy Cheese Sauce ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Return the now empty pan to medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Add the garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @flour{½%tbsp}, then add the @creme fraiche{65%g} and @water{50%ml}.

Bring to the boil, lower the heat and add the @grated Italian style hard cheese{1%unit}. Stir until the cheese is melted and the sauce starts to thicken, ~{1%minute}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper. Remove the pan from the heat.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, reheat the sauce if needed.

Share the chicken schnitzels between plates.

Serve the rosemary roast potatoes and @salad leaves{40%g} alongside, with the creamy sauce in a small bowl.

Finish the salad with a drizzle of @balsamic glaze{1%sachet}.